==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orgyia
<hw>Or*gy"i*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ the length of the outstretched arms. So named because, when
at rest, it stretches forward its fore legs like arms.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>. <def>A genus of bombycid moths whose caterpillars
(esp. those of <spn>Orgyia leucostigma</spn>) are often very injurious
to fruit trees and shade trees. The female is wingless. Called also
<altname>vaporer moth</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

